LETTER OF PETER TO PHILIP (4)

And the apostles answered and said: “Lord, we will do everything you have commanded us, for you are our Lord and our God.” Then the Lord departed from them in peace. And the apostles gathered together and went up to Jerusalem. And they gave thanks to the Father and to the Son and to the Holy Spirit, glorifying YHWH.
Then Peter said to Philip: “Our brother Philip, the Lord has commanded us to go out into the world and preach the gospel of the kingdom. Let us therefore divide the regions among us and go forth in the power of YHWH.” And they all agreed.
Philip answered and said: “My brother Peter, the Lord has appeared to me and said, ‘Philip, go and preach the gospel of the kingdom in all the world.’ Therefore I will go to the region that has been appointed to me.” And Peter blessed him.
The apostles gathered together and prayed, saying: “O Lord, give us power and strength that we may go forth and preach your gospel in all the world, as you have commanded us.” And a great light appeared and the Lord stood in their midst and said to them: “Peace be with you. Go forth and preach the gospel of the kingdom. I am with you always.”
Then the apostles said to the Lord: “Lord, you have commanded us to go into the world and preach the gospel. Tell us therefore how we should preach and what we should say to the people.” The Lord answered and said: “Go and preach the gospel of the kingdom. I have given you power and authority over all the power of the enemy. Heal the sick, cast out demons, and proclaim that the kingdom of heaven is at hand.”

