Allogenes (2)

And the great Invisible Spirit, the Father of the All, the One who is ineffable and unknowable, the One who is beyond all thought and all silence — He is the source of all. He is the root of the All. He is the Light that is in the Light. He is the Life that is in the Life. He is the Mind that is in the Mind. He is the One who is before the All. He is the All, and He is above the All.
Allogenes said: “I was in the great aeon of the Barbelo, and I saw the divine Autogenes. I saw the Triple-Powered One, the great Invisible Spirit who is above all. I saw the glory of the One who is hidden. I saw the light that is in the light. I saw the life that is in the life. I saw the mind that is in the mind. I saw the silence that is in the silence. I saw the unknowable One who is before the All.”
And the great Invisible Spirit said to Allogenes: “You have seen the glory of the One who is before the All. You have seen the Triple-Powered One. You have seen the Barbelo. You have seen the divine Autogenes. You have seen the light that is in the light. You have seen the life that is in the life. You have seen the mind that is in the mind. You have seen the silence that is in the silence. You have seen the unknowable One who is beyond all thought.”
Then Allogenes said: “I am Allogenes, the stranger. I have come to know the One who is before the All. I have seen the glory of the Invisible Spirit. I have seen the Triple-Powered One. I have seen the Barbelo and the divine Autogenes. I have seen the light, the life, the mind, and the silence that are in the light, the life, the mind, and the silence. I have seen the unknowable One who is beyond all thought and all silence.”
And the great Invisible Spirit said: “Blessed are you, Allogenes, for you have known the One who is before the All. You have seen the glory of the unknowable One. You have seen the Triple-Powered One. You have seen the Barbelo and the divine Autogenes. You have seen the light, the life, the mind, and the silence. Go now and proclaim what you have seen to those who are worthy.”

GOSPEL OF JUDAS (1)

Then Judas said: “I know who you are and from where you have come. You are from the immortal realm of Barbelo. But I am not worthy to utter the name of the one who has sent you.” And Yeshua said to him: “Step away from the others and I shall tell you the mysteries of the kingdom. It is possible for you to reach it, but you will grieve much.”
The twelve disciples said to Yeshua: “We have seen you in a vision, for you appeared to us in a dream.” Yeshua answered: “Why have you been troubled? Truly I say to you, no generation of this aeon will know me.”
Then Judas said to him: “Teacher, what is the fruit of the knowledge of the tree?” Yeshua said: “The fruit of the tree is the knowledge of good and evil. Adam ate of it and brought death into the world. But I have come to bring life.”
Yeshua said: “The rulers of this world are blind. They do not know the truth. But you, Judas, will exceed all of them. For you will sacrifice the man that clothes me, so that my inner body may be released.”
The disciples said: “Master, where will you go?” Yeshua said: “I go to the place from which I came. You will seek me but not find me.”
Then Judas said: “Teacher, as you have listened to all of them, now listen to me. I have seen a great vision.” Yeshua said: “Tell me your vision.”
Judas said: “I saw myself as the twelfth disciple. The others were stoning me.” Yeshua said: “You will be cursed by the other generations, but you will come to rule over them.”
Yeshua said: “Judas, you will exceed all of them. For you will sacrifice the man that clothes me.”
