Codex Tchacos Introduction

These are the secret words of revelation given to the chosen ones in the last days. The Codex Tchacos preserves the hidden teachings of the Anointed and the Gnostic vision of the divine realms. Let the one who has ears to hear, hear. Let the one who seeks the light, find it. The words of Judas, Allogenes, Peter to Philip, and the resurrection mysteries are preserved here for the elect.
The great Invisible Spirit, the Father of the All, the unknowable One who is beyond all thought and silence, has revealed these mysteries through His Son and through the holy apostles. Blessed is the one who reads and understands these words, for they lead to the knowledge that saves.
In the name of the Father, the Mother, and the Son, and the holy aeons of the Barbelo, these writings were preserved in the desert for the generation that would come at the end of the age. The one who seeks the truth will find it here.
The Codex Tchacos contains the Gospel of Judas, the revelation of Allogenes, the letter of Peter to Philip, and the book of the resurrection. These are the hidden teachings given to the disciples in secret, to be revealed only to those who are worthy.
